text: Hans Haselböck (26 July 1928 – 20 October 2021) was an Austrian organist, composer, author and academic teacher. He was organist at the Dominican Church, Vienna, for 65 years. He was professor of organ and improvisation at the Vienna Music Academy.Kirchenmusik-Pionier Hans Haselböck verstorben (in German) Diocese of Vienna, 21 October 2021 ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1928 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Austrian composers Category:Austrian writers Category:Austrian academics Category:Austrian organists
